title.rendered: IND vs NZ 3rd T20I Highlights: IND-NZ Match Ends In A Tie; IND Win Series 1-0

content.rendered:
The third and final T20I between India and New Zealand ended in a draw as India (75/4 in 9 overs) tied for the DLS result. Due to the lack of time, before the match resumed, the referee decided to abandon the match and it ended in a draw. Earlier, India lost the wicket of Ishan Kishan, Rishab Punt, Shreyas Ayer, and Suryakumar Yadav, and the 161-run chase was shaken early against New Zealand in the third T20I.

Mohammed Siraj and Arshdeep Singh took 4 wickets each as India bundled New Zealand for 160. Devon Conway and Glenn Phillips scored the 50s with the New Zealand national team, while the Indian national team died in his show bowling. Earlier, India had struck early as Ashdeep Singh sacked Finn Allen and sacked Mark Chapman blaming Siraj. Previously, New Zealand won the toss and chose to bat first in their third and final T20I at McLean Park in Napier.
